{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"313","heading":"Nontraditional and Emerging Transportation Technology Council","label":"313 Nontraditional and Emerging Transportation Technology Council","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/stI/ch3/schI","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextThe date of enactment of this section, referred to in subsecs. (a) and (d), is the date of enactment of , which was approved .Pub. L. 117–58Nov. 15, 2021"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—Establishment","label":"a .—Establishment","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Not later than 180 days after the date of enactment of this section, the Secretary of Transportation (referred to in this section as the “Secretary”) shall establish a council, to be known as the “Nontraditional and Emerging Transportation Technology Council” (referred to in this section as the “Council”), to address coordination on emerging technology issues across all modes of transportation.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Membership.—","label":"b Membership.—","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":".—In general","label":"1 .—In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fb%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Secretary, who shall serve as an ex officio member of the Council;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fb%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Deputy Secretary of Transportation;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fb%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Under Secretary of Transportation for Policy;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fb%2F1%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Assistant Secretary for Research and Technology of the Department of Transportation;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fb%2F1%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Assistant Secretary for Budget and Programs of the Department of Transportation;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"F","heading":null,"label":"F","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1/F","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fb%2F1%2FF","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the General Counsel of the Department of Transportation;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"G","heading":null,"label":"G","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1/G","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fb%2F1%2FG","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Chief Information Officer of the Department of Transportation;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"H","heading":null,"label":"H","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1/H","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fb%2F1%2FH","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Administrator of the Federal Aviation Administration;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fb%2F1%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Administrator of the Federal Highway Administration;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"J","heading":null,"label":"J","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1/J","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fb%2F1%2FJ","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Administrator of the Federal Motor Carrier Safety Administration;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"K","heading":null,"label":"K","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1/K","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fb%2F1%2FK","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Administrator of the Federal Railroad Administration;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"L","heading":null,"label":"L","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1/L","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fb%2F1%2FL","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Administrator of the Federal Transit Administration;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"M","heading":null,"label":"M","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1/M","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fb%2F1%2FM","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Administrator of the Maritime Administration;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"N","heading":null,"label":"N","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1/N","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fb%2F1%2FN","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Administrator of the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"O","heading":null,"label":"O","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1/O","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fb%2F1%2FO","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Administrator of the Pipeline and Hazardous Materials Safety Administration; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"P","heading":null,"label":"P","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1/P","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fb%2F1%2FP","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any other official of the Department of Transportation, as determined by the Secretary.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Chair and vice chair.—","label":"2 Chair and vice chair.—","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":".—Chair","label":"A .—Chair","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fb%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Deputy Secretary of Transportation (or a designee) shall serve as Chair of the Council.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":".—Vice chair","label":"B .—Vice chair","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fb%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Under Secretary of Transportation for Policy (or a designee) shall serve as Vice Chair of the Council.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":".—Duties","label":"c .—Duties","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/c/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fc%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"safety oversight;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/c/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fc%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"environmental review; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/c/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fc%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"funding and financing issues;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"coordinate the response of the Department of Transportation to nontraditional and emerging transportation technology projects;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"engage with stakeholders in nontraditional and emerging transportation technology projects; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/c/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fc%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"develop and establish Department of Transportation-wide processes, solutions, and best practices for identifying and managing nontraditional and emerging transportation technology projects.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":".—Best Practices","label":"d .—Best Practices","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"publish initial guidelines to achieve the purposes described in subsection (c)(4); and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"promote each modal administration within the Department of Transportation to further test and support the advancement of nontraditional and emerging transportation technologies not specifically considered by the Council.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":".—Support","label":"e .—Support","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Office of the Secretary shall provide support for the Council.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"f","heading":".—Meetings","label":"f .—Meetings","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/f","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Ff","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Council shall meet not less frequently than 4 times per year, at the call of the Chair.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"g","heading":".—Lead Modal Administration","label":"g .—Lead Modal Administration","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/g","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fg","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/g/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fg%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"designate a lead modal administration of the Department of Transportation for review of the technology, mode, or project; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/g/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fg%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"arrange for the detailing of staff between modal administrations or offices of the Department of Transportation as needed to maximize the sharing of experience and expertise.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"h","heading":".—Transparency","label":"h .—Transparency","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313/h","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t49/s313","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft49%2Fs313%2Fh","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Not later than 1 year after the date of establishment of the Council, and not less frequently than annually thereafter until , the Council shall post on a publicly accessible website a report describing the activities of the Council during the preceding calendar year.December 31, 2026","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
